---
layout: base.njk
permalink: /speakers.html
title: Speakers
description: Everyone who has presented at a European Security Studies Conference, across every edition since 2017, with the papers they gave each year.
navKey: ""
lang: en
alternates:
  en: /speakers.html
---
{%- set t = i18n[lang or "en"] -%}

<header class="page-header">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="eyebrow">The ESSC corpus</span>
    <h1>Speakers</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">
      Everyone who has presented at a European Security Studies Conference, drawn
      from the programmes of every edition. {{ corpus.stats.speakerCount }}
      speakers across {{ corpus.stats.editions }} conferences, {{ corpus.stats.paperCount }}
      papers in all. Listed by surname; the affiliation shown is the most
      recent on record. Use the site search to find a specific name.
    </p>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="speaker-toolbar">
      <label class="speaker-filter">
        <span>Theme</span>
        <select data-speaker-theme>
          <option value="">All themes ({{ corpus.stats.speakerCount }})</option>
          {%- for t in corpus.themes %}
          <option value="{{ t.name }}">{{ t.name }} ({{ t.count }})</option>
          {%- endfor %}
        </select>
      </label>
      <nav class="speaker-az" aria-label="Jump to letter">
        {%- for L in corpus.letters %}
        <a href="#ltr-{{ L }}">{{ L }}</a>
        {%- endfor %}
      </nav>
    </div>

    <p class="speaker-noresult" data-speaker-noresult hidden>No speakers match that theme.</p>

    <ol class="speaker-index" role="list" data-speaker-list>
      {%- for s in corpus.speakers %}
      {%- set prevLetter = corpus.speakers[loop.index0 - 1].letter if not loop.first else "" %}
      {%- if s.letter != prevLetter %}
      <li class="speaker-letter" role="presentation" data-speaker-letter="{{ s.letter }}">
        <h2 id="ltr-{{ s.letter }}" class="speaker-letter-h">{{ s.letter }}</h2>
      </li>
      {%- endif %}
      <li class="speaker-entry" data-speaker-entry data-themes="{{ s.themes | join('|') }}">
        <p class="speaker-name" lang="en">
          {%- if s.profileUrl %}<a href="{{ s.profileUrl }}">{{ s.display }}</a>
          {%- else %}{{ s.display }}{% endif %}
          {%- if s.profileUrl %} <span class="speaker-badge">EISS member</span>{% endif %}
        </p>
        {%- if s.affiliation %}
        <p class="speaker-aff muted" lang="en">{{ s.affiliation }}</p>
        {%- endif %}
        {%- if s.themes.length %}
        <p class="speaker-themes">
          {%- for th in s.themes %}<span class="speaker-theme-chip">{{ th }}</span>{% endfor %}
        </p>
        {%- endif %}
        <details class="speaker-papers">
          <summary>{{ s.count }} contribution{% if s.count != 1 %}s{% endif %}{% if s.firstYear %} · {{ s.firstYear }}{% if s.lastYear != s.firstYear %}–{{ s.lastYear }}{% endif %}{% endif %}</summary>
          <ul role="list">
            {%- for p in s.papers %}
            <li>
              <span class="speaker-paper-conf"><a href="{{ p.conferenceUrl }}">{{ p.conferenceLabel }}{% if p.year %} {{ p.year }}{% endif %}</a></span>
              <span class="speaker-paper-title" lang="en">{{ p.title }}</span>
            </li>
            {%- endfor %}
          </ul>
        </details>
      </li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ol>

    <p class="muted" style="margin-top: var(--space-6); font-size: var(--fs-sm); max-width: 44rem;">
      Assembled from the published conference programmes. Names are matched
      conservatively, so a person who appears under noticeably different
      spellings across years may show more than once. Themes are inferred
      from the panel each paper sat in (the nine permanent EISS sections
      plus recurring themes); papers in a generically-titled session are
      left untagged rather than guessed.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<script src="{{ '/assets/js/speaker-filter.js' | bust }}" defer></script>
